<section id="channels">
  <div class="wrap">
    <p class="skick">Wherever you are</p>
    <h2 class="sh">Text her like a friend — <em>it's all still here</em>.</h2>
    <p class="sintro">
      Zuly isn't trapped in an app. Reach her the way you already talk. However you message her, it
      lands in one private thread you'll always find in the app.
    </p>
    <div class="pillars" style="margin-top:2rem">
      <div class="pil" style="--pc:var(--oxblood)">
        <span class="pn">In the app</span>
        <h3>Most private</h3>
        <p>Your deepest conversations, fully encrypted. The safe place for the real things.</p>
        <span class="ev">End-to-end encrypted</span>
      </div>
      <div class="pil" style="--pc:var(--oxblood)">
        <span class="pn">On WhatsApp</span>
        <h3>Like a voice note to a friend</h3>
        <p>Chat or send a voice note from wherever you are. Warm, familiar, encrypted.</p>
        <span class="ev">Voice &amp; chat</span>
      </div>
      <div class="pil" style="--pc:var(--gold)">
        <span class="pn">By text</span>
        <h3>Quick capture, anywhere</h3>
        <p>"Hey Zuly, add milk" or a morning check-in — no app to open. Perfect for the small stuff.</p>
        <span class="ev">Your own private number</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p style="margin-top:1.3rem;font-size:.86rem;color:var(--faint)">
      Every number is yours alone, verified to your account — so your thread stays private to you. We're
      always honest about which channels are encrypted and what that means.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
